description:
Moonstone serves up a brand-new demonic trilogy! an otherworldly creature cries out for redemption-Then, a frustrated priest, tired of exorcising the same entity time and again, decides to turn the tables. And finally, find Lost Loves in a time and place where the streets are alive with magic.

Installment of the horror anthology series focused on demons. First appearance of the Twilight Crusade's Succubus.

Table of Contents:

"Nocturnal Slave"

Written by: Joe Gentile

Illustrated by: Eddy Newell

Lettered by: Chuck Maly

"Humanic Possession"

Written by: David Rust

Illustrated by: Ken Wheaton

Lettered by: George Broderick

"Lost Loves"

Written by: James Lowder

Illustrated by: Brett Barkley

Lettered by: Leslie A. Barkley

The script for the story "Lost Loves" was a finalist for the 2004 Stoker Award for Best Illustrated Narrative. http://www.horror.org/stokerwinnom.htm#2004
name: Demons

description:
The final chapter in the critically acclaimed, best-selling New Krypton storyline that began in the SUPERMAN family of comic book titles in 2008, written by James Robinson (STARMAN) and Sterling Gates (SUPERGIRL).

A war is coming, and all that stands between Earth and 100,000 vengeful supermen is one Superman! The storyline the SUPERMAN books have been building to since 2008 has arrived. The Man of Steel must stop the two worlds he loves from destroying each other, while General Sam Lane and all of Earth's heroes make one last stand against General Zod and his army of super-powered Kryptonians. The fate of two worlds will be decided here. In the end, can Superman save either?

Collects WAR OF THE SUPERMEN #1-4 and SUPERMAN #700.
name: HC/TPB

description:
A short story focusing on Wesker and Dr. Doom's plan to merge their respected worlds for conquest.

It also includes; character art, campaign art, promotional art and fan art.

Acclaimed as one of the best new series of 2006, the first edition of Harvey Award Winning Best Writer Ed Brubaker and Scream Award Winning Best Artist Sean Phillips ground-breaking new series is finally here! Collecting the sold-out and hard-to-find first arc “Coward” promises to be one of the trade highlights of the year, and readers of these white-hot creators other projects, such as Daredevil, Captain America, and Marvel Zombies will not want to miss it!

Coward is the story of Leo, a man who can plan and execute almost any heist, but only if he can convinced the plan is safe enough. But sometimes the reward is worth the risk, and when a woman from Leo’s past comes to him with a sure-fire score to nab a few million worth of diamonds from Police Evidence, all his rules and cautions go right out the window. But in the world Leo lives in, as he may soon learn, those rules may be the only thing keeping him alive.
name: Vol. 1

description: The post-apocalyptic Dungeons & Dragons setting’s first ever comic continues! Beneath a crimson sun lie wastelands of majestic desolation and cities of cruel splendor where life hangs by a thread. Welcome to Athas! In Part 2 of “Ianto’s Tomb,” a runaway gladiator and part-time slave hunter slog their way across the Athasian desert toward the city of Tyr... and more trouble.
name: 2 (of 5)

description:
This volume contains the critically acclaimed fourth graphic novel based on the White Wolf role-playing game: "Giovanni." Also includes three never-before-seen stories: "Assamite," Lasombra," and "Tremere." Tales of hidden motives, lost treasures, assassinations, and judgment. What more could you want?

Table of Contents:

  • "Giovanni: The Machiavelli Conundrum" by Robert Weinberg and Richard Clark
  • "Tremere: The Book of Damages" by David Gallaher and Andy Bennett
  • "Lasombra: Passion Play" by James Lowder and Vince Locke
  • "Assamite: The Sleep of Reason" by Eric Griffin, Stefan Petrucha, Jerry DeCaire,
name: Blood & Shadows

description:
DARK SNAKE EYES brings COBRA straight to The Pit, bringing the battle to G.I. JOE's home turf.

Can the Joes withstand the assault led by one of their own or will COBRA finally bring them to their knees?

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: A Prise warrior demands that Claudio starts looking ahead of himself, to his destiny. But maybe he should look over his shoulder, too, because Al the Killer is lurking right behind him! At the same time a greater evil will arise, one that will play a major role in Claudio's future!

volume.name: The Amory Wars: In Keeping Secrets of Silent Earth: 3

description:
A CHRISTMAS EVE HEIST STORY - JUST IN TIME FOR THE HOLIDAYS.

Tracy Lawless has come home for his first Christmas in the city in nearly twenty years. But the only kind of family reunion he'll find is in a graveyard, because his last living relative, his little brother Ricky, was killed almost a year earlier. Now Tracy is back to find out who did it, and why, and to do that he'll have to immerse himself back into the criminal world that he once ran away from. The question is, even if he finds the answers he seeks, will he survive the experience?

Winner of the EISNER AWARDS for Best Writer and Best New Series!
name: Vol. 2

description: Ariana's two worlds have now officially collided! Her life in shambles because of her cover story, Ari gets a surprise from her mother than may prevent her from taking part in her mission. Oh, and did we mention the nuclear bomb?
name: Codename: Noob, Part Four

description: The game is afoot as Sherlock Holmes and his strange group of allies race against the clock to counter Count Dracula's moves in London against the Royal Family. Will their efforts be enough to stop a darkness spreading over the newly rebuilt London? Elementary, my dear reader!

After real estate agent Richard Ashwalt refuses to sell the house of a horrendous murder to elderly gentleman Jebediah Crone, his life takes a turn for the worse. Accused of first-degree murder, Richard flees his home and his family to find Crone and clear his name - but his nightmares are getting worse and the line between dream and reality is beginning to blur...
name: 2 (of 6)

description:
For detective-exorcist Alice Hotwire, waking in a jail cell is an unwelcome flashback to youth.

With Bertus Rantz and his team of private contractor ghost-hunters out to win a permanent city contract by any means necessary, Alice must first escape to keep the job she hates, then compete with Rantz to capture a blue-light possessed robot and rescue the injured woman he has taken hostage.

Can Alice outwit Rantz, who has little intention of bringing them in 'alive,' save the hostage, and return safely home to her boyfriend from hell?
name: Everyone Gets A Medal

description:
Winner of the Eisner Award for Best New Series, and Winner of the Harvey and Eisner Awards for Best Writer! The third collection of Ed Brubaker and Sean Phillips' critically-acclaimed noir series follows a different twist of the knife this time -- telling three interlinking stories that take place during the early 1970s and swirl around the fate of a hard-luck Femme Fatale, a boxer and a thief and killer just home from Vietnam. Each story is told from a different narrative point-of-view, so we can see the varied secrets and hidden desires that ultimately lead to a lot of murder and mayhem.

With an introduction by award-winning writer/director John Singleton (Boyz N the Hood, Shaft).
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: Criminal: The Dead and the Dying

description:
Years ago Jacob's life was torn apart, and now one bad decision on one bad night may shatter what little he's got left. A searing tale of sex, obsession, greed and insanity by best-selling creators Ed Brubaker and Sean Phillips!

Introduction done by Ken Bruen.
name: Vol. 4
